------------------------------------------------------------------
KEY LESSON
------------------------------------------------------------------

For PNG steganography challenges involving LSB, zsteg is a
one-command solution. Install it with gem install zsteg and run
it on any suspicious PNG. It checks b1 through b8 across all
channel combinations and prints anything that decodes to
readable text. If zsteg finds nothing, move to StegSolve for
manual bit plane inspection. LSB data is invisible to the eye
but trivially detected by these tools.
